# Code Quality Standards

## Formatting (Biome Configuration)
- 2-space indentation
- 100 character line width
- Double quotes for strings
- Always use semicolons
- ES5 trailing commas
- LF line endings

## Linting Rules
- Follow Biome recommended rules
- No explicit `any` types (error level)
- Organize imports automatically
- Enable all suspicious code detection

## TypeScript Best Practices
- Use strict mode settings from [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
- Prefer explicit type annotations
- Use ES modules consistently
- Enable source maps for debugging

## File Organization
- Keep utilities in `utils/` directory
- Use descriptive file names
- Group related functionality together
- Maintain clear separation of concerns

## Error Handling
- Use proper error boundaries
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Handle async operations gracefully
- Validate inputs with Zod schemas
